or samples per authored intent chain:\n# Case_excluded == 'No' and Histologic_type in {'Endometrioid', 'Serous'}.\neligible = [\n    row for row in records\n    if row.get('Case_excluded') == 'No' and row.get('Histologic_type') in {'Endometrioid', 'Serous'}\n]\n\n# Keep histology types that have FIGO_stage values among eligible rows.\nhisto_with_figo = {\n    row['Histologic_type']\n    for row in eligible\n    if row.get('FIGO_stage') not in ('', 'NA')\n}\neligible = [row for row in eligible if row.get('Histologic_type') in histo_with_figo]\n\n# Age >= 70\nolder = [\n    row for row in eligible\n    if row.get('Age') not in ('', 'NA') and float(row['Age']) >= 70\n]\n\ncounts = Counter(\n    row['FIGO_stage'] for row in older if row.get('FIGO_stage') not in ('', 'NA')\n)\n\nprint('count_by_FIGO_stage')\nfor stage, count in counts.items():\n    print(f'{stage}\\t{count}')\nprint('most_frequent')\nprint(counts.most_common(1)[0][0] if counts else None)\n", "reason": "Adjusted the filtering logic to match the authored intent chain: use Case_excluded == 'No' and Histologic_type restricted to Endometrioid/Serous, then apply Age >= 70 and count non-missing FIGO_stage values before printing the most frequent stage. Also kept output printing explicit as requested."})
